08/10/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Deputy Chief Prosecutor Milorad Cvijovic has been arrested for suspected forgery and involvement in a corruption scandal, the interior ministry announced on Saturday (October 7th).
Cvijovic is accused of forging a document to enable local businessman Slobodan Radulovic to buy shares in a supermarket chain at a steep discount.
Nine people have been arrested since April in connection with the probe.
Radulovic, however, remains at large.
(Beta, RTS, AFP - 07/10/06)
